No argument can take away how Jesus has replaced your heart of stone with a heart of flesh.

222
00:18:52,540 --> 00:19:00,760
No argument can take away how Jesus has opened your eyes to the plight of the poor, the lost, and the hurting.

223
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:08,130
No argument can take away how Jesus has taken away your hate and your anger and allowed you to forgive.

224
00:19:08,130 --> 00:19:14,770
give. No argument can take away how Jesus has helped you become a more loving and connected

225
00:19:14,770 --> 00:19:22,710
parent, grandparent, friend, son, and daughter. No one can take that away. No argument can take

226
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:31,330
away how Jesus has replaced your fear with hope and a future. Don't ever underestimate the power

227
00:19:31,330 --> 00:19:37,750
of a life that's been touched by Jesus. And so I am here as your pastor and your friend to

228
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:42,270
encourage you. Don't let anybody beat you down with arguments. If you have an encounter with

229
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:50,560
Jesus, you tell it with boldness because nobody can take that away. Your life with Jesus is a

230
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:59,640
powerful testimony of God at work, and you don't have to be ashamed. Tell the story freely and with

231
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:14,880
boldness. Lesson number two, following Jesus leads to worship. It leads to worship. When the man

232
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:21,180
finally understands who Jesus is. He's been a disciple, say the Pharisees, when He finally

233
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:27,280
understands who Jesus really is, He falls down and says, Lord, I put my faith in You.

234
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:37,730
And then what happened? He worshiped. Worshiped. I have this image that He fell down on His face

235
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:45,910
and He worshiped. The eyes of His heart were finally opened. He could see Jesus,

236
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:55,070
Jesus, Jesus the Son of God. Not just the healer, but Jesus the Son of God. And now this blind man

237
00:20:55,070 --> 00:21:02,940
who was physically in the dark can see reality with his eyes, and he can see reality with his

238
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:12,150
heart. He can really see. He has real vision of what is happening around him. Friends, when you

239
00:21:12,150 --> 00:21:18,650
decide to really follow Jesus and let His Spirit take over your life, you are drawn into worship.

240
00:21:19,590 --> 00:21:26,500
You can't really help it. You're drawn to worship. Worship is expressing your love to God.

241
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:32,700
Worship is giving God His due. Worship is an experience of reaffirming the way things really

242
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:37,780
are, that God is awesome and holy, and let's be honest, we're selfish and hard-hearted.

243
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:40,990
God is in control.

244
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:42,170
We're not.

245
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:44,600
God loves us first.

246
00:21:45,390 --> 00:21:46,670
We love Him back.

247
00:21:47,230 --> 00:21:50,950
Worship reorients those realities in our lives.

248
00:21:53,710 --> 00:21:55,150
What's your attitude towards worship?

249
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,660
Is your heart drawn into worship?

250
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:03,920
Does something block your interest in worship?

251
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:09,560
Is there a stumbling block on your journey with Jesus?

252
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:17,010
because to be a follower of Jesus is to be a pilgrim that delights in worshiping God,

253
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:21,090
who delights in giving God glory, who delights in giving God honor,

254
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:23,630
who delights in giving God praise.

255
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:26,180
That's what a disciple is all about.

256
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,720
This man became a disciple, and he worshiped.

257
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:41,070
And finally, the third lesson we learn is that following Jesus is about healing your blind spots.

258
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:45,090
You know about blind spots.

259
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:49,220
It's when you're about to change lanes, right?

260
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:53,600
You look in the mirror, it all looks clear.

261
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:59,680
But you happen to look over your shoulder just as they told you to back when you got your license,

262
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:03,160
and sure enough, there's a car right there.

263
00:23:03,980 --> 00:23:05,800
Because they were in your blind spot.

264
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,360
There are places where you cannot see.

265
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:12,550
And if you're not careful, you can cause quite a stir.

266
00:23:13,550 --> 00:23:18,490
I also like those little experiments that you're told how to, you know, like close one eye,

267
00:23:18,490 --> 00:23:22,270
of look at a dot on the page and a letter to the left or right will suddenly

268
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:26,270
disappear as it hits the fovea in the back of your eye. There's a blind

269
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:30,370
spot in the back of your retina where the actual optic nerve leaves and if

270
00:23:30,370 --> 00:23:34,370
you find it by doing these little experiments and looking and raising the page in and

271
00:23:34,370 --> 00:23:37,390
out, you can actually watch a letter disappear right off the page.

272
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:42,860
Go try it. It's kind of interesting. There's probably a website telling you how to do that.

273
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:48,180
Blind spots prevent us from seeing.

274
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:52,670
We can have blind spots in our heart as well.

275
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:59,270
You see, in this story, like most of the stories in the book of John, there's another irony.

276
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:05,290
The irony here is the blind person recognizes who Jesus is, whereas those with eyes fail to see.

277
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:07,240
They have blind spots.

278
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:13,920
The Pharisees had all the knowledge, but they had a blind spot about who Jesus really was.

279
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,180
Their vision was obscure.

280
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:19,620
They're looking right at him, but they're really not seeing.

281
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:22,660
Now, blind spots can have a lot of causes.

282
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:29,440
and a wise person is one that begins to say, Holy Spirit, look into my heart and clean out

283
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:36,700
my blind spots. Where is it that I'm holding an idea that's not about your kingdom? Where am I

284
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:42,230
holding a prejudice that's not about what you're about? Where am I holding onto a hurt or a pain

285
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:52,620
that you want to clear out, and I'm just blind to it? I just don't see it. Sometimes blind spots

286
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:54,780
come from people who've taught us.

287
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:56,380
They can come from parents or teachers

288
00:24:56,380 --> 00:24:59,080
or even sermons.

289
00:24:59,260 --> 00:25:01,320
They come from home environments.

290
00:25:01,460 --> 00:25:03,020
They come from your classrooms.

291
00:25:03,140 --> 00:25:05,940
You can get blind spots as people pour into you

292
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,660
the untruths, things that are not of the kingdom

293
00:25:08,660 --> 00:25:10,340
can get rooted in our hearts.

294
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:12,100
Wise people say,

295
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:15,880
Lord, make me see, really.

296
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,460
Clear out the blind spots in my own heart.

297
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,370
The Pharisees got hung up on the issue of Sabbath.

298
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:23,930
It's an important issue.

299
00:25:23,930 --> 00:25:25,730
God actually said that in the Ten Commandments.

300
00:25:26,090 --> 00:25:28,710
But, you know, something good can prevent something even better.

301
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:30,890
And they missed it.

302
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:32,500
They missed it.

303
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:40,980
When you follow Jesus, when you let him into your life, he will show you your false beliefs,

304
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:46,080
your prejudices, your hypocrisies, the attitudes that hold you back and that dishonor God

305
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:47,920
and your fellow human beings.

306
00:25:48,220 --> 00:25:53,490
And if you really get honest, you can say, Lord, please heal my blind spots

307
00:25:53,490 --> 00:25:57,540
and allow you to see as God sees.

308
00:25:58,670 --> 00:26:01,210
with his eyes, with his heart.

309
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:06,490
And when you follow Jesus, your blind spots begin to be healed.

310
00:26:09,180 --> 00:26:12,220
I like what this gentleman, Frederick Buechner, has to say.

311
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:13,860
He's a Presbyterian, but that's okay.

312
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,000
He can teach us a lot of things.

313
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:18,020
Listen to what he says.

314
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:23,770
People are prepared, he writes, for everything except for the fact

315
00:26:23,770 --> 00:26:28,730
that beyond the darkness of their blindness, there is a great light.

316
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,520
They are prepared to go on breaking their backs,

317
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:37,040
plowing the same old field until the cows come home without seeing,

318
00:26:38,010 --> 00:26:40,090
until they stub their toes on it,

319
00:26:40,090 --> 00:26:44,410
and there's a treasure buried in that field rich enough to buy Texas.

320
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:49,080
They are prepared for a God who strikes hard bargains,

321
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:55,300
but not for a God who gives as much for an hour's work as for a day.

322
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:59,580
They are prepared for a mustard seed kingdom of God,

323
00:26:59,580 --> 00:27:06,540
no bigger than the eye of a newt but not for the great banyan it becomes with birds in its branches

324
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:14,350
singing mozart they are prepared for the plot for the potluck at first presbyterian

325
00:27:14,350 --> 00:27:24,390
but not for the marriage supper of the lamb isn't that rich are you blind to the miracles that god

326
00:27:24,390 --> 00:27:32,620
is performing in your midst do you settle for second best are blind spots keeping you from

327
00:27:32,620 --> 00:27:38,060
really seeing what God is up to. Do you know what your

328
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:42,650
purpose in life is? Are you blind to that? Do you know why you're here?

329
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:46,570
Do you know where you're going? Do you know what life is about? I will say it's about

330
00:27:46,570 --> 00:27:49,770
giving testimony to the greatness of God.

331
00:27:51,730 --> 00:27:55,710
That to know what life is about is about worshiping God and enjoying Him

332
00:27:55,710 --> 00:28:00,610
forever. Life is about being spiritually healed by God

333
00:28:00,610 --> 00:28:04,170
and becoming all that He desires for you.

334
00:28:04,170 --> 00:28:06,890
be all that he wants for you

335
00:28:06,890 --> 00:28:09,500
that's what life's about

336
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:11,780
living with God's size vision

337
00:28:11,780 --> 00:28:13,690
is what it's about

338
00:28:13,690 --> 00:28:16,630
and so I conclude this morning

339
00:28:16,630 --> 00:28:18,030
I just want you to hear this

340
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:21,620
this poem by Sir Francis Drake

341
00:28:21,620 --> 00:28:24,640
and may this be a prayer

342
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,590
of yours as well

343
00:28:26,590 --> 00:28:29,040
disturb us Lord

344
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:32,220
when we are too well pleased

345
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:33,140
with ourselves

346
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:36,570
when our dreams have come true

347
00:28:36,570 --> 00:28:38,450
because we've dreamed too little

348
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:43,370
when we arrive safely because we've sailed too close to the shore.

349
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:49,300
Disturb us, Lord, when the abundance of things we possess,

350
00:28:49,820 --> 00:28:53,030
we've lost our thirst for the waters of life.

351
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:57,700
Having fallen in love with life, we've ceased to dream of eternity.

352
00:28:59,010 --> 00:29:01,090
And in our efforts to build a new earth,

353
00:29:01,670 --> 00:29:04,690
we've allowed our vision of the new heaven to dim.

354
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:09,320
Disturb us, Lord, to dare more boldly,

355
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:14,660
to venture on wider seas where storms will show your mastery.

356
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:18,260
Where losing sight of land, we shall find the stars.

357
00:29:19,820 --> 00:29:22,580
We ask you to push back the horizons of our hopes

358
00:29:22,580 --> 00:29:29,260
and to push us into the future in strength, courage, hope, and love.

359
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:31,220
Let's pray.

360
00:29:33,390 --> 00:29:34,770
Lord, that's what we want to be about.

361
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,110
We don't want to be too safe.

362
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:43,030
We want to see as you see and have God-sized visions for life

363
00:29:43,030 --> 00:29:46,600
and for ministry, we want to have a testimony.

364
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,340
We want to be people that share that with boldness.

365
00:29:50,450 --> 00:29:52,170
We want our blind spots healed.

366
00:29:53,540 --> 00:29:56,560
We want to be about worship, for that's what you created us.

367
00:29:58,540 --> 00:30:03,210
So, Father, I pray that these truths would sink into our heads

368
00:30:03,210 --> 00:30:04,370
and also to our hearts.

369
00:30:06,340 --> 00:30:09,020
They would germinate within us and sprout.

370
00:30:11,860 --> 00:30:12,760
They would grow us.

371
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,480
Father, may you grow us.

372
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:20,380
And I pray that you would stiffen us by your Spirit,

373
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:23,080
to share testimony boldly in this world.

374
00:30:26,780 --> 00:30:28,900
Father, may you bring people into our lives.

375
00:30:29,760 --> 00:30:31,860
As Steve has encountered this mercenary,

376
00:30:31,980 --> 00:30:34,400
may you bring the most unlikely people into our lives.

377
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:36,560
And may we not be afraid,

378
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:41,060
but may our testimony and your spirit in us

379
00:30:41,060 --> 00:30:43,240
drive us to share it boldly

380
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:46,570
and to worship God fully

381
00:30:46,570 --> 00:30:49,740
and to be all about the things

382
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:51,400
that you want to be about in our lives.

383
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,520
Thank you, Lord, that we were blind, but now we see.

384
00:30:56,700 --> 00:30:59,460
So may these truths become our realities.

385
00:31:00,710 --> 00:31:02,970
We live these kinds of lives as disciples.

386
00:31:04,870 --> 00:31:07,890
Be about your kingdom in a powerful way.

387
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:15,340
Father, I pray that you would accomplish your purposes today with these people and with me.

388
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:18,090
Thank you for the testimony of your word.

389
00:31:19,380 --> 00:31:20,560
May it be powerful in our lives.

390
00:31:22,260 --> 00:31:25,900
And I pray that you, Lord, would just move amongst this place as we sing amazing grace.

391
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:30,100
That you teach us again how much you love us.

392
00:31:31,020 --> 00:31:33,240
How great and good your grace really is.

393
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:36,970
and if anybody needs to find that grace this morning

394
00:31:36,970 --> 00:31:38,810
I pray that they would give their life to you

395
00:31:38,810 --> 00:31:41,380
and in this, just a simple act of prayer

396
00:31:41,380 --> 00:31:44,910
of saying Lord I'm thankful for what you did on the cross

397
00:31:44,910 --> 00:31:46,550
I'm sorry for my life

398
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:48,310
where I've been and what I've done

399
00:31:48,310 --> 00:31:49,790
but now I get a fresh start

400
00:31:49,790 --> 00:31:52,340
thank you that you're healing me

401
00:31:52,340 --> 00:31:54,860
opening my eyes to see truth

402
00:31:54,860 --> 00:31:56,740
and it's you Jesus

403
00:31:56,740 --> 00:32:03,670
Father may those prayers happen as you lead

404
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:09,220
I pray you accomplish your purposes Father

405
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:11,260
in Jesus name we pray

406
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:12,780
Amen.

407
00:32:14,290 --> 00:32:15,630
Let's stand and sing this song.

